pub/AUIS/patches/official

README

The patches located in this directory should be applied using the patch program.  Sources for the patch program are available in pub/AUIS/util. 

The patches currently available for release 6.3 are: 

patch.631 - for all users 
	See Aug. 27 info-andrew mail with subject: 	AUIS Release 6.3.1 Available
patch.hp - for HP users only 
	See Sept. 8 info-andrew mail with subject: 
	Patch for HP Users
patch.632 - for all AMS users
	See October 27 info-andrew mail with subject:  	AUIS Patch 6.3.2
patch.633 - for all users 
	 Patch to V6 figure to make it accept 
	figures created with later versions, including 	C++ versions 7.2 and higher.  
patch.634 - for eatmail/AMS/Messages users
	Fixes potential cause of coredumps for anyone 
	who users eatmail or has AMS/Messages
	configured to read mail from a UNIX-style
	mail spool. 

Previous posts to info-andrew are archived in the pub/AUIS/ia-archive directory on ftp.andrew.cmu.edu.  

Apply the patches from the top-level AUIS directory, i.e., the directories overhead, atk, ams, exist.  Once you have the patch program, issue the following command to csh: 

	patch -p < /{PathToFile}/{PatchFileName}

Note:  omitting the -p flag will cause patch to not be able to find the correct file to fix.  

If you do not have the patch sources, they can be found on a number of ftp servers.  We make them available on our ftp server, ftp.andrew.cmu.edu, in  pub/AUIS/util/patch.tar.Z.   

Kindly report bugs you encounter to info-andrew-bugs@andrew.cmu.edu.  Technical questions or questions about using AUIS should be directed to the info-andrew@andrew.cmu.edu distribution list, while general information can be obtained by sending mail to info-andrew-request@andrew.cmu.edu. 

